-- China May Introduce Weather Insurance This Year to Aid Farmers, Daily Says
-- Bloomberg News
-- 2010-07-20T00:16:54Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-20/china-may-introduce-weather-insurance-this-year-to-aid-farmers-daily-says.html

          
          
             China may introduce weather
insurance before the end of this year to help farmers cope with
economic losses, the China Daily reported today, citing an
unidentified insurance company official.  
 The insurance policies will first be introduced on a trial
basis in Fujian province, which is frequently hit by typhoons,
the newspaper reported.  
          
          


  


        